(based on 1 penultimate and numerous prepenultimate instar larvae). Body (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA08751FE8B4842FEB5" box="[273,375,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="28.[264,367,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-68@28.[265,1322,406,1750]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 11. Left lateral views of Hebridosimulium species larvae. Last-instar larvae, except l &amp; n, which are penultimate. Arrowheads indicate dorsal tubercles. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071417" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071417/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 11i</figureCitation>
): total length ca. 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA08420FE8B4BF1FEB5" box="[608,708,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="6.1">6.1 mm</quantity>
; females evenly mottled grey, with metathoracic segment slightly orange, males more yellowish. Head (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA085E5FEA34D25FE6D" box="[933,1040,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="31.[264,367,1399,1423]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,326,1375]" captionTargetId="figure-179@31.[264,1323,326,1375]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 14. Dorsal views of larval heads of Hebridosimulium species. steatopygium species group. Last instars, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate instars. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071423/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 14d</figureCitation>
): anterior frontoclypeal apotome markedly pale; labral fan stalks pale to light brown; head-spot pattern positive, medial head spots in Eiffel Tower configuration, ecdysial lines pale and distinct; width 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA08748FE2B4840FE15" box="[264,373,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
, length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA08796FE2B4B76FE15" box="[470,579,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.65">0.65 mm</quantity>
; distance between antennal bases 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA0859CFE2B4D7CFE15" box="[988,1097,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
; lateral margins of head subparallel; posterior edge of apotome markedly emarginated; postocciput extended between distinct cervical sclerites emarginated apotome. Antenna: distal article light brown, remainder pale; total length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA08484FD934A00FD9D" box="[708,821,604,630]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.44">0.44 mm</quantity>
; distal article 0.3 times as long as basal articles, extended well beyond labral fan stalk. Labral fan: stalk very light brown, anterior palatal bar markedly developed; 47 rays, 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF1FFA084B7FD634A54FD2D" box="[759,865,684,710]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.70 mm</quantity>
in length, 16–19 rays less substantial; microtrichia 1.3 times longer than ray width, distinct pattern of 6 smaller microtrichia to 1 larger one. Postgenal cleft (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA0840DFD334B80FCFD" box="[589,693,764,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="34.[264,367,1395,1419]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,327,1371]" captionTargetId="figure-185@34.[264,1323,326,1371]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 17. Postgenal clefts and hypostoma of larvae of Hebridosimulium species. Last instar except b, d, &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071429/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 17d</figureCitation>
): arrowhead shaped, 1.3 times deeper than wide with slightly convex edges; posteroventral elongated muscle spots positive. Postgenal bridge: 0.4 times as long as cleft depth, bridge pale yellow; ventral genae and postgenae light brown. Hypostoma (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA0844FFCBB4BB4FC65" box="[527,641,884,910]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="36.[264,367,1407,1431]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,326,1379]" captionTargetId="figure-153@36.[264,1323,326,1383]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 19. Hypostomal teeth of larvae of Hebridosimulium species. Last instar, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071435/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 19d</figureCitation>
): overall cone-shaped; ratio 4.4; teeth not markedly protruded anteriorly; median tooth prominent, lateral teeth small, directed anteriorly, but scalloped medially; medial sublateral teeth larger, others smaller with subsidiary basal tooth; paralateral teeth just apparent; lateral serrations essentially absent; 9 hypostomal setae per side. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA08409FBDB4B80FBC5" box="[585,693,1044,1070]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="43.[264,367,1401,1425]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,327,1377]" captionTargetId="figure-171@43.[264,1323,326,1377]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 21. Mandibular teeth of larvae of Hebridosimulium species, steatopygium species group. Last instar, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071439" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071439/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 21d</figureCitation>
): apical teeth normally developed, 6 spinous teeth; spinous teeth gap normal; serration and sensillum broadly based and distinct; blade region smooth and straight. Abdomen: expanded evenly posteriorly to 5th abdominal segment, slightly steatopygous; posterodorsal tubercles absent. Posterior circlet: directed posteriorly; 180 rows of hooks; 28–30 hooks per row (total ca. 5,200).
</paragraph>
