</paragraph>
<paragraph id="940D9A4BFFF1FFA08748F95B48B6F946" blockId="74.[264,1323,1684,1870]" box="[264,387,1684,1709]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF1FFA08748F95B48B6F946" box="[264,387,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="940D9A4BFFF1FFA18778F9734AA8FE3D" blockId="74.[264,1323,1684,1870]" lastBlockId="75.[264,1323,284,470]" lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
This species is found in the same riverine habitat as 
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF1FFA085FBF9734D1DF93E" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[955,1064,1724,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="banksi">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF1FFA085FBF9734D1DF93E" box="[955,1064,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">S. banksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF1FFA0827BF9734D91F93D" box="[1083,1188,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="82.[264,367,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,314,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-136@82.[264,1323,314,1490]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURE 23. Habitats of larvae of Hebridosimulium species, Vanuatu. a. Santo, Sarakata River, UNELCO Hydro Station. Type locality of S. callipygium. Note limestone substrate. b. Santo, Upper Sarakata River, Millennium Cave region. Typical habitat of S. callipygium and S. subparadisium. c. Malekula, Wesso River, downstream of cascade. Type locality of S. spiroi. Note travertine substrate. d. Banks Islands, Vanua Lava, Tahiti River. Type locality of S. banksi and S. undulatum. e. Tanna, stream south of Bethel. Type locality of S. johnfrumi. f. Malekula, Pankumu River. Type locality of S. pankumuense. g. Efate, Ewor River, La Cressionnière. Type locality of S. tuberculum. Note the travertine terraces." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071447/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 23d</figureCitation>
). Although described only from one penultimate instar larva and some earlier instar larvae, 
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF1FFA08354F92B48B0F8CE" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatum">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF1FFA08354F92B48B0F8CE" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">S. undulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered here a separate species — one related to the 
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF1FFA08273F8C34DFAF8CE" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[1075,1231,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steatopygium">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF1FFA08273F8C34DFAF8CE" box="[1075,1231,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">steatopygium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF1FFA08725F8FB4B54F8A6" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[357,609,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatum">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF1FFA08725F8FB4B54F8A6" box="[357,609,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Simulium undulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a markedly emarginated apotome posteriorly. It is expected that in the last-instar larva, the emarginations will be even more developed, because they increase in size from earlier to later larval instars. With lack of reared adult material from the Banks Islands simuliids (
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF0FFA18543FEA34A59FE6E" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[771,876,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="banksi">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF0FFA18543FEA34A59FE6E" box="[771,876,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">S. banksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF0FFA1853BFEA34DFEFE6E" box="[891,1227,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF0FFA1853BFEA34D10FE6E" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[891,1061,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callipygium">S. callipygium</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53B2E1C8FFF0FFA18271FEA34DFEFE6E" authorityName="Craig &amp; Currie &amp; Hunter &amp; Spironello" authorityYear="2006" box="[1073,1227,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatum">S. undulatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
), adults collected by Cheesman in the late 1920s from Vanua Lava and deposited in the 
<collectionCode id="F2A3028EFFF0FFA182B5FE5B4C13FE45" box="[1269,1318,404,430]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bristol Museum" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">BM</collectionCode>
, cannot as yet be assigned to species (see 
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF0FFA184A8FE734ABEFE3E" box="[744,907,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Incertae sedis</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
